name: NYDailyNews
text:
Brooklyn Assembly candidate Emily Gallagher admitted to mooning a couple having sex when she was 19.

According to a post she wrote, she spotted a couple having sex through a window and stopped to watch, then mooned them when they noticed.
https://t.co/bPFlkID0RW

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Former Jets bust Christian Hackenberg is trying to play pro baseball.

His coach said he hit 92 mph with his fastball, but is consistently at 90.

“I know how hard it is to hit a baseball," Hackenberg said, "but I have the arm talent.”
https://t.co/1LFDbeotWB

name: NYDailyNews
text:
The billionaires who own the 30 MLB teams were never negotiating with their players.

They are getting the joke of a short season they wanted all along — the bare minimum number of games the owners are willing to finance.
https://t.co/xwCbGEXcDc

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Officials launched an investigation into the death of Robert Fuller, a black man found hanged from a tree in California.

Police said evidence suggested Fuller died by suicide, but hundreds of people protested saying they don’t trust the local authorities.
https://t.co/ybLOppSAbS

name: NYDailyNews
text:
The EU struck a deal for 400 million doses of an experimental coronavirus vaccine with drug giant AstraZeneca.

The drugmaker is working with Oxford scientists to produce and distribute the potential vaccine, which is currently in tests among 10K Brits.
https://t.co/OIPXc7Cbim

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Trump vowed to boycott U.S. soccer — just like he's done with the NFL — if players kneel in protest of racism.

“I won’t be watching much anymore!” Trump wrote on Twitter.
https://t.co/aqETK4QNbE

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Britney Spears statues should replace New Orleans’ Confederate ones, one petition says.

Among the highlights the petition points to are Spears’ donations to Louisiana flood victims.
